parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to lose structural integrity, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the frame
especially in the rear suspension area
and loose or detached control arms.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Swaying or loss of control while driving
loud noises or vibrations from the rear suspension
and broken or detached control arms or mounts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower ball joint can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Swaying or loss of control while driving
loud noises or vibrations from the front suspension
and broken or detached ball joints.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: especially near the rear trailing arm bracket
and gas tank area. The vehicle may wobble or sway uncontrollably while driving
and may exhibit unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine overheating, oil leaks, and engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially life-threatening accidents.
Oil sludge buildup can cause engine damage, overheating, and premature wear, leading to costly repairs and potentially life-threatening accidents.
Exhaust system failure can cause loud noises, decreased performance, and potentially life-threatening accidents due to loss of control.
Air conditioning compressor failure can cause the vehicle to lurch forward, leading to loss of control and potentially life-threatening accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle lurches forward when air conditioning compressor engages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake pad failure can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Grinding noises when brakes are applied
hairline cracks on the brake pads
brake pads need to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS system failure can cause loss of control, extended stopping distances, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: ABS system fails to work properly
vehicle continues to travel after applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake pedal issues can cause loss of control, extended stopping distances, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rotors can cause vibration when braking, reduce braking performance, and potentially lead to accidents.
Unusual brake noise can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, potentially leading to reduced braking performance and accidents.
symptoms: grinding noises when brakes are applied.
